'''Glomerulocystic kidney disease''' ('''GCKD''') is a [[cystic]] disorder of the [[kidney]]s. GCKD involves cystic dilation of [[Bowman's capsule]].<ref>{{cite journal |last=Bissler |first=John J. |last2=Siroky |first2=Brian J.|last3=Yin |first3=Hong |date=October 2010 |title=Glomerulocystic kidney disease |journal=Pediatric Nephrology |publisher= |volume= 25|issue= |pages=2049–2059 |doi= 10.1007/s00467-009-1416-2|pmc=2923715 |pmid=20091054}}</ref> It can occur with or without congenital abnormality.<ref>{{cite journal |last=Miyazaki |first=K |last2=Miyazaki |first2=M | last3=Yoshizuka |first3=N| last4=Sasaki |first4=O | date=May 2002 | title=Glomerulocystic kidney disease (GCKD) associated with Henoch-Schoenlein purpura: a case report and a review of adult cases of GCKD |journal=Clinical Nephrology |publisher=Dustri-Verlag |volume=57 |issue=5 |pages=386–391 |doi= }}</ref>
