[[File:Otaniemen vesitorni 1.JPG|thumbnail|Otaniemi water tower in 2010]]
'''The Otaniemi water tower''' is a structure designed by the well-known Finnish architect [[Alvar Aalto]] in 1971.<ref name="HSY. Water towers.">{{cite web|title=HSY. Water towers.|url=http://www.hsy.fi/en/waterservices/water_management_networks/Pages/water_towers.aspx|publisher=Helsinki Region Environmental Services Authority|accessdate=15 October 2013}}</ref> The water tower is located in [[Otaniemi|Otaniemi area]], [[Espoo]], [[Finland]]. <ref name="HSY. Water towers."></ref> The total capacity of the tower is 6000 m³. <ref name="HSY. Water towers."></ref>

